{{Multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=July 2015}} {{update|date=December 2018}} }}
'''FocusVision''' is a [[market research]] technology [[company]] specializing in [[Quantitative research|quantitative]] and [[qualitative research]]. The company, which was founded in 1990, previously specialized in live [[video]] transmission of qualitative [[research]]. In 2014, 2015 and 2016, the company acquired the leading technology companies: [[Revelation (disambiguation)|Revelation]], [[Decipher (disambiguation)|Decipher]], [[ResearchReporter]], [[Qualvu]] and [[Kinesis (disambiguation)|Kinesis]].<ref>http://www.research-live.com/focusvision-buys-revelation-to-merge-qual-technology/4011763.article</ref><ref>http://www.mrweb.com/drno/news20267.htm</ref><ref>http://www.mrweb.com/drno/news20592.htm</ref><ref>http://www.mrweb.com/drno/news21875.htm</ref> This expanded the company's offerings to include complete [[end-to-end]] technology solutions for quantitative research, qualitative research, reporting, [[project management]], panel management and more.
==Company Growth== The company has grown from 80 full-time employees to more than 400 and is headquartered in [[Stamford, Connecticut]]. With its recent growth, FocusVision has expanded globally beyond its headquarters in [[Connecticut]], to include offices in [[California]], [[Texas]], [[Oregon]] and global locations in the [[United Kingdom]], [[Brazil]], [[Australia]], [[Bulgaria]] and [[Singapore]].<ref>https://www.focusvision.com/contact/</ref>
==Recent Case Studies== FocusVision has conducted several recent research studies resulting in [[white papers]] covering mobile video optimization in partnership with [[America Online]];<ref>http://www.onlinemr.com/focusvision-and-aol-white-paper-on-survey-design-for-mobile-video/</ref> mobile research design;<ref>http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/245805/focusvision-white-paper-says-surveys-must-be-mobil.html</ref> and methodology for conducting a quantitative-qualitative joint research project with [[Lightspeed Research]] and [[The Family Room LLC.]]<ref>http://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/245805/focusvision-white-paper-says-surveys-must-be-mobil.html</ref>
==Awards and Accolades== FocusVision won a [[Stevie Award]] for Company of the Year in the 2015 [[American Business Awards]].<ref>http://www.stevieawards.com/pubs/awards/403_2183_25748.cfm</ref> The company was also ranked on the 2015 GRIT 50 Most Innovative Suppliers in Market Research.<ref>http://www.greenbookblog.org/2015/06/09/2015-grit-top-50-the-50-most-innovative-suppliers-in-market-research/</ref>
