{{Linguistics}} The tables below provide a list of foreign languages most frequently taught in American schools and colleges. They reflect the popularity of these languages in terms of the total number of enrolled students in the [[United States]]. (Here, a [[foreign language]] means any language other than [[English language|English]], and includes American Sign Language.)
== Lists == Below are the top foreign languages studied in [[Education_in_the_United_States#K.E2.80.9312_education|public K-12 schools]] (i.e., primary and secondary schools). The tables correspond to the 18.5% (some 8.9 million) of all K-12 students in the U.S. (about 49 million) who take foreign-language classes.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |url=http://www.actfl.org/sites/default/files/pdfs/ReportSummary2011.pdf |title=Foreign Language Enrollments in K–12 Public Schools |date=February 2011 |publisher=American Council on the Teaching of Foreign Languages (ACTFL) |access-date=October 17, 2015}}</ref>
=== K-12 === {|class="wikitable" |+K-12 students (2007-2008) ! Rank ! Language ! Enrollments ! Percentage |- | align=center| 1 | [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | align=right| 6,418,331 | align=right| 72.06% |- | align=center| 2 | [[French language|French]] | align=right| 1,254,243 | align=right| 14.08% |- | align=center| 3 | [[German language|German]] | align=right| 395,019 | align=right| 4.43% |- | align=center| 4 | [[Latin]] | align=right| 205,158 | align=right| 2.30% |- | align=center| 5 | [[Japanese language|Japanese]] | align=right| 72,845 | align=right| 0.82% |- | align=center| 6 | [[Italian language|Italian]] | align=right| 65,058 | align=right| 0.73% |- | align=center| 7 | [[Standard Chinese|Chinese]] | align=right| 59,860 | align=right| 0.67% |- | align=center| 8 | [[American Sign Language]] | align=right| 41,579 | align=right| 0.46% |- | align=center| 9 | [[Russian language|Russian]] | align=right| 12,389 | align=right| 0.14% |- | align=center| | Others<ref>"Others" includes (in order of quantity) Native languages, Korean, Portuguese, Vietnamese, Arabic, Hebrew, Polish, Swahili, Turkish.</ref> | align=right| 255,825 | align=right| 2.87% |- | | '''Total''' | align=right| '''8,907,201''' | align=right| '''100%''' |}
