The '''M-2''' visa is a type of [[Travel visa|visa]] reserved for the spouse or child of an [[M-1 visa|M-1]] student.
An M-2 spouse may not work or engage in full-time schooling unless it is recreational.<ref>"[https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/8/214.2 8 CFR 214.2(m)(17)(ii)]". ''via Legal Information Institute, Cornell University Law School''. Retrieved November 16, 2018.</ref> An M-2 child may engage in full-time schooling at the primary or secondary level.<ref>"Immigration pocket field guide". ''Matthew Bender & Company, Inc''. p. 41.</ref>
