'''Marburn Academy''' is a [[non-profit]] [[Private school|independent day school for students in grades 2–]][[K-12 school|12 school]] in [[New Albany, Ohio]]. The school was created in 1981, with the goal of providing a nurturing educational environment for above average students who had struggled with traditional schooling. Education at the school geared towards children struggling with [[Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder|ADHD]], [[dyslexia]] and/or executive function issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=Marburn History: Location, Affiliations, Accreditations {{!}} Marburn Academy|url=http://www.marburnacademy.org/about-marburn/history/|website=Marburn Academy|accessdate=May 21, 2017|language=en|date=25 February 2016}}</ref> The school prides itself on being one of 13 accredited [[Orton-Gillingham]] schools in the [[United States]], and its 100% acceptance rate of its high school students to colleges.<ref>{{cite web|title=Marburn Difference {{!}} Scientifically Validated Teaching Methods {{!}} Marburn Academy|url=http://www.marburnacademy.org/academics-programs/unique-instruction/|website=Marburn Academy|accessdate=May 21, 2017|language=en|date=17 March 2016}}</ref>
In January 2017, Marburn Academy moved from [[Forest Park East]], Columbus, to a new location at 9555 Johnstown Road, [[New Albany, Ohio]] 43054.
